definitions.definition: Something that is fixed in place, especially a permanent appliance or other item of personal property that is considered part of a house and is sold with it; compare fitting , furnishing .
examples: The residence was sold with fixtures and fittings.

definitions.definition: A regular patron of a place or institution; a person constantly present at a certain place.
A work-holding or support device used in the manufacturing industry.
A state that can be recreated, used as a baseline for running software tests .
